          "title": "Common Mistakes Review",
          "text": "In English, we say 'a car' or 'a uniform' because singular countable nouns need an article. We also say 'a lot of money' in positive sentences, not 'much money'. Words like 'information' and 'homework' are uncountable, so they never have an -s. Also, adjectives are always singular and come before the noun.",
